ENUGU – Four men suspected to be involved in the murder of the traditional ruler of Ogbozinne community, Igwe Stephen Nwatu, in Nkanu West Local Government Area of Enugu state have been arraigned before an Enugu East Magistrate Court. The suspects were arraigned at the Enugu East Magistrate Court 1, Enugu Magisterial District, presided over by Chief Magistrate 1. D.K Ekoh. The suspects identified as Uchenna Edeh, Joseph Okenwa, Leonard Nnam and Nnemba Comfort Okenwa were arraigned on a count charge of Conspiracy and Murder. They were remanded in prison custody while awaiting the advice of the Director of Public Prosecution (DPP). Meanwhile, one Nnajiofor Nwatu believed to have participated in the act was said to have been nabbed and he is helping the police in their investigation, just as a manhunt for others have been intensified. It would be recalled that the late Monarch was gruesomely murdered on June 11, 2018 by some persons identified as members of his community. Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 